<HEADLINE>
FT  09 DEC 93 / World News in Brief: Saunders' complaint to be examined
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The European Commission of Human Rights agreed to take up a complaint by
former Guinness chairman Ernest Saunders that he was given an unfair trial
in Britain in 1990 on company fraud charges.
</TEXT>
