<HEADLINE>
FT  09 DEC 93 / Observer: Mixed grille
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Spare a tear for the directors who waved goodbye to their company cars last
year. An Institute of Directors and Reward Group survey on director's pay
discloses that the number of directors with company cars is down this year
to 63 per cent from last year's 79 per cent.
As those who dream of Direct Line salaries kiss goodbyes to their
four-wheeled friends, they can perhaps take comfort from the fact that some
standards are not falling; the Jaguar is still the director's favourite,
followed by Mercedes.
