<TEXT>
Five per cent of employers use teleworkers, and half of those employ some
form of home-based worker, says a Department of Employment report on 1,000
organisations, Lisa Wood writes.
The report says the idea that teleworking is spreading steadily is 'open to
doubt'. It says: 'There is a shifting population of schemes which come and
go in response to changing individual and corporate requirements.'
