<TEXT>
Bosnian government envoys in London yesterday launched a bitter attack on
the British government for refusing to lift the arms embargo, and deplored
the UN's threats to withdraw humanitarian aid if a political settlement were
not found, writes Gillian Tett.
Their comments, made at the start of a conference on Bosnia, came after
