FT  08 DEC 93 / International Company News: Hoogovens share issue raises Fl
362m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP-DJ
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   AMSTERDAM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Hoogovens, the Dutch steelmaker, said its two-stage issue of new share
certificates over the past week raised Fl 362m (Dollars 190m), AP-DJ reports
from Amsterdam.
The company said the offer was oversubscribed. Proceeds will be used to
shore up Hoogovens' capital base. All 9.05m share certificates on offer were
placed. The issue price was Fl 40 per certificate.
Certificates are a unique Dutch form of depositary receipt representing
shares that many companies in the Netherlands place with trusts friendly to
management as an anti-takeover defence.
