FT  08 DEC 93 / International Capital Markets: SBC in Mexico venture
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LAURIE MORSE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CHICAGO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Swiss Bank Corporation and Mexico's largest private financial group, Grupo
Financiero Banamex-Accival, are to form an alliance to trade Mexican equity
derivative products.
SBC said the move would strengthen its presence in Mexico, where it expects
to see more initial public offerings and investments by global money
managers.
Starting next year, the joint venture plans to make markets in
over-the-counter options on equities, exchange-listed warrants, futures and
forwards, equity swaps and convertibles.
Grupo Financiero's two main subsidiaries are the National Bank of Mexico and
Accival, the securities broker.
