<TEXT>
Reynolds Metals, the US aluminium group, is considering restructuring some
of its operations, mainly in the fabricating area. It wants to improve
worldwide performance in 'extremely difficult market conditions' in the
aluminium industry, Reuter reports.
The actions could result in charges of between Dollars 150m and Dollars 225m
