FT  08 DEC 93 / International Company News: Power Corp in Dollars 45m
Chinese investment
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Power Corp of Canada, the chief holding company of Montreal financier Mr
Paul Desmarais, and China International Trust and Investment have formed a
50/50 joint venture to invest an initial CDollars 60m (USDollars 45.4m) in a
new industrial park at Pudong near Shanghai, writes Robert Gibbens.
CITIC-Power Investments, based in Hong Kong, will take a two-thirds interest
in the park with one-third owned by Shanghai Zhangjiang Hi-Tech Park
Development.
</TEXT>
