<HEADLINE>
FT  08 DEC 93 / UK Company News: Julian Hodge Bank hits Pounds 8.13m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROLAND ADBURGHAM, Wales and West Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Profits of Julian Hodge Bank, the family-owned Cardiff bank, rose from
Pounds 5.32m to a record Pounds 8.13m pre-tax in the year to October 31.
The figure included a surplus on investment sales of Pounds 3.38m (Pounds
1.3m).
The bank, which specialises in commercial and industrial lending, is chaired
by Mr Julian Hodge, son of Welsh financier Sir Julian Hodge who founded the
bank seven years ago.
Mr Hodge said the bank had increased its deposit base by a quarter to Pounds
24.7m despite a period of low interest rates. Shareholders' funds had more
than doubled since 1988 to stand at Pounds 48.4m.
'The current economic outlook is the most promising for a number of years,'
he said.
</TEXT>
