<HEADLINE>
FT  08 DEC 93 / UK Company News: Holmes &amp; Marchant recovers to Pounds 1.25m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Holmes &amp; Marchant Group, the marketing services company, reported pre-tax
profits of Pounds 1.25m for the year to September 30, against losses of
Pounds 4.76m. The improvement was accentuated by the comparative figure
being restated for FRS 3.
Lower exceptional costs of Pounds 294,000 (Pounds 3.02m) and a lower charge
for discontinued activities of Pounds 10,000 (Pounds 2.96m) were the main
factors behind the improvement. Net interest payable fell to Pounds 826,000
(Pounds 1.08m).
Turnover fell to Pounds 32.3m (Pounds 33.6m) but operating profit rose to
Pounds 2.38m (Pounds 2.3m). Earnings per share came out at 4.1p (losses
18.9p).
On prospects the company said there was little evidence that recessionary
pressures were easing.
