<HEADLINE>
FT  08 DEC 93 / UK Company News: AG Holdings beats forecast with Pounds
2.91m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
In its first results since coming to the market in June, AG Holdings, which
makes rope and cable reels, beat its prospectus forecast of Pounds 2.7m with
a pre-tax profit of Pounds 2.91m for the 12 months to July 31.
Turnover of Pounds 15.8m compared with Pounds 10.7m at March 31.
Earnings per share came out at 11.4p and there is a special dividend of 2p
as forecast in the listing.
</TEXT>
