<HEADLINE>
FT  08 DEC 93 / UK Company News: All-round upturn at Martin Shelton
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
An upturn in business across the product range enabled Martin Shelton, the
USM-quoted diaries, calendars, gifts and betting office equipment supplier,
to swing from losses of Pounds 144,000 to profits of Pounds 90,000 pre-tax
for the half year ended September 30.
The shares responded via a 12p rise to 80p.
Sales improved from Pounds 1.68m to Pounds 2.1m. Earnings worked through at
1.18p (losses 1.88p) and the interim dividend is lifted to 1.25p (0.75p).
</TEXT>
